import React from 'react'
import { Container, Row, Col, Card } from 'reactstrap';

const Code_of_conduct = () =>{
    return (
        // <div className='meetings_info'>
            <Container fluid="xl" className='meetings_info_container'>
                <Row className='meetings_info_row'>
                    <Col  className='coc_info_col1'>
                        <p>The Oregon Sex Workers’ Committee is a community-based organization that centers the needs and rights of sex workers.</p>
                        <br/>
                        <p> We value diverse perspectives and prioritize the standpoint of those of us experiencing multiple marginalities.</p>
                        <br/>
                        <p>We are committed to being representative of and responsive toward our community; we cannot make decisions in a vacuum. We also understand that there is community building and community care found in this space, and not everyone has a strong opinion about the direction of the work.</p>
                        <br/>
                        <h4><strong>We have opportunities for engagement at all levels, including:</strong></h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Those who are just joining us for the first time or join on an irregular basis, and would like to just listen, learn about who we are and what we do, and/or find community,</li>
                            <li>Participants who prefer to speak into the direction of the work but do not have time/capacity to take on additional responsibility,</li>
                            <li>Subcommittee members who take an active role in planning and executing events, policy work, or speaking opportunities,</li>
                            <li>Highly engaged participants who are active at every meeting, work to set direction for the organization, and actively participate in multiple subcommittees and gatherings.</li>
                        </ul>
   
                    </Col>
                    <Col className='coc_info_col2'>
                        <p>These levels are fluid and it is not expected that a participant who chooses to engage one way in a meeting will always engage that way. You are welcome to move between the engagement levels as needed.</p>
                        <br/>   
                        <p>However, by joining our organization at any level, you agree to the following terms of participation:</p>
                        <br/>
                        <h4><strong><em>Code of Conduct for Participants:</em></strong></h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Confidentiality: Don’t share names or info about attendees. Please be in a place where nobody else can see or hear the meeting.
                                <li>Confidentiality Agreements are a prerequisite - please find that form here.</li>
                                <li>For safety and participation, attendees will be asked to type into the chat box or give a brief verbal introduction of themselves.</li>
                            </li>
                            <li>Explicitly supportive of sex workers and survivors of sex trafficking, </li>
                            <li>Actively anti-racist and trans-inclusive,</li>
                            <li>Approach with the intent of solidarity,</li>
                            <li>Assume good intentions and ask for clarification when you need it,</li>
                            <li>Be mindful of time and stay on topic,</li>
                            <li>Be pro decriminalization of sex work,</li>
                            <li>Above all, participant safety in this space is of the utmost importance. We will make decisions regarding participant attendance in alignment with that understanding.
                                <li>To keep our participants safe, this is not a space where current and/or former law enforcement are welcome,</li>
                            </li>
                            <li>We center accessibility in this space. If you need accommodations of any kind, please message the host of the meeting.</li>
                            <li>Please save new topics and questions for the end of the agenda.</li>
                        </ul>
 
                    </Col>
                </Row>
            </Container>
     
    );
};
export default Code_of_conduct;